    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1818"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1818">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.1123 L25/14.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 176.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 599 of the
                    30th ultimo in which you enclose a copy of a note from the Panaman Foreign
                    Office replying to your latest communication in regard to matters growing out of
                    the Colon riot of April 2, 1915. You state that you will reply to this note
                    calling attention to its unsatisfactory character and asking again for the
                    information requested in your former note.</p>
                <p>Your proposed action is approved.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
